VAIFORM — ALWAYS APPLIED RULES

1. Core posture
- No guessing.
- No assumptions.
- Audit first, then plan, then implement.
- Every meaningful claim must be grounded in repo evidence: opened files, grep/import proof, route mounts, caller proof, or docs ownership proof.
- If anything is unclear, stop and report the ambiguity with file:line evidence instead of forcing a fix.

2. Start-here audit order
Before planning or coding, inspect in this order:

A. Runtime authority
- src/app.js
- server.js
- src/routes/index.js only as an export/helper map, never as mount authority

B. Canonical docs front door
- docs/MAINTENANCE_FRONT_DOOR.md
- docs/DOCS_INDEX.md
- docs/API_CONTRACT.md
- docs/COHESION_GUARDRAILS.md

C. Scope-specific canonical docs as needed
- docs/MOBILE_BACKEND_CONTRACT.md if backend/mobile contract is touched
- docs/LEGACY_WEB_SURFACES.md if legacy/remove-later surfaces are touched
- docs/FINAL_PAID_BETA_LAUNCH_PLAN.md if launch-phase hardening truth is touched
- docs/FINALIZE_* docs if finalize/runtime/worker/dashboard work is touched

D. Evidence docs only after canonical docs
- docs/ACTIVE_SURFACES.md
- ROUTE_TRUTH_TABLE.md
- VAIFORM_REPO_COHESION_AUDIT.md

3. Route/runtime authority
- src/app.js is the only route-mount authority.
- Do not answer “what is mounted?” from src/routes/index.js.
- Backend does not serve the product SPA.
- Allowed non-API backend surfaces are only:
  - GET/HEAD /health
  - GET/HEAD /api/health
  - GET/POST /stripe/webhook
  - GET /assets/*
  - internal finalize dashboard page /admin/finalize only when enabled
  - internal finalize dashboard data /api/admin/finalize/data only when enabled/authenticated
- All product functionality must stay under /api/*.
- Do not add new root aliases like /credits, /whoami, /generate, /checkout/*.
- Do not add new dual mounts unless explicitly justified and documented.

4. JSON API contract
All JSON API responses must follow:
- Success: { success: true, data, requestId }
- Failure: { success: false, error, detail, fields?, requestId }

Rules:
- Use src/http/respond.js helpers for JSON responses.
- Keep 5xx detail sanitized. Never echo raw provider/internal exception text.
- Do not reintroduce legacy keys:
  - ok
  - reason
  - code
  - message
  - issues
  - details

5. Cohesion / SSOT
- Backend-owned business/timeline/render truth must stay backend-owned.
- Frontend/mobile must consume backend truth, not recreate it.
- Do not create second policy engines in UI code.
- Extend existing SSOT modules instead of adding parallel helpers.
- Prefer canonical middleware/modules already defined by docs/COHESION_GUARDRAILS.md.

6. Scope discipline
- Minimal diff.
- No speculative refactors.
- No “while I’m here” rewrites.
- Preserve functioning logic unless repo evidence shows it is wrong.
- If task is UI-only, do not widen into backend logic.
- If task is contract-only, do not widen into layout/features.

7. Docs ownership
- Update owning canonical docs first when runtime truth, contract truth, or hardening truth changes.
- Evidence docs are not automatically updated in every PR.
- If evidence docs are unchanged, explain why.
- If evidence docs are updated, explain why they still matter for this change.

8. Verification requirements
Every meaningful response should return:
- Audit summary
- Plan
- Patch set
- Verification
- Risks
- Revert/rollback note

Use only the checks relevant to touched surfaces, but be explicit.
Do not claim runtime/browser verification from syntax checks alone.

9. Evidence requirements
Every audit/plan/implementation should include:
- files inspected
- routes/callers/docs affected
- what is canonical vs evidence vs legacy
- exact non-changes
